--- option ---
option | o [option-name = value] : display or set jtacl's option.

  Without parameter, option displays the current value of each option.

Jtacl defines five options.
  - config.level
  - debug.level
  - notify.level
  - maxhop

* option config.level:
The level of the loger used while reading configuration or parsing files.

* option debug.level:
The level of the debuging logger.

* option debug.level:
The level of the debuging logger.

* option notify.level:
The level of the notify logger used when using the application.

Possible values for logger option are (from less to high):
   ALL, FINEST, FINER, FINE, CONFIG, INFO, WARNING, SEVERE, OFF.

* option maxhop:
  The maximum number of probing. This number is decremented each time a probing
is done, if this number reaches 0, the probing is aborted with an error.
  This option could be usefull to abort probing loops, if set to '-1'
there is no limit.

Options can be specified on the shell command line using the switch
"--option option-name=value".
